book-text-medal-instructions =[head=1][color=#8B0000]Medal Descriptions & Award Criteria[/color][/head]

[color=#4682B4]Defender of the Homeland Medal[/color]
Awarded to enlisted soldiers who have demonstrated dedication, reliability, and distinguished service to the New California Republic. Most commonly presented to soldiers and cadets.

[color=#4682B4]Crimson Cross Medal[/color]
Awarded to NCR medical personnel who have shown exceptional skill, professionalism, and commitment in the treatment and care of others.

[color=#4682B4]Ironhammer Medal[/color]
Awarded to NCR engineers who have distinguished themselves through technical expertise, maintenance of vital infrastructure, or outstanding field support.

[color=#4682B4]Brahmin Brain Medal[/color]
A lighthearted and unofficial distinction awarded to personnel whose actions, decisions, or misadventures have become particularly memorable across the Republic.

[color=#4682B4]Predator Medal[/color]
Awarded to fighters who have successfully eliminated dangerous threats or completed especially difficult operations under hazardous conditions. Most commonly awarded to assault troops and frontline personnel.

[color=#4682B4]Longstride Ribbon[/color]
For scouts, rangers, or personnel who gather critical intelligence or survive dangerous expeditions beyond NCR territory.[/color]

[color=#4682B4]Bronze Bear Medal[/color]
Awarded to fighters who have displayed notable courage, resilience, or bravery in the line of duty. Commonly presented to rank-and-file NCR personnel.

[color=#4682B4]Golden Bear Medal[/color]
One of the Republic’s highest distinctions, awarded to personnel who have shown exceptional leadership, outstanding service, or significant contributions to the NCR. Most commonly presented to distinguished sergeants and senior personnel.[/color]

book-text-medal-information = [head=1][color=#8B0000]Notice from NCR Headquarters[/color][/head]

[color=#FF0000]Attention personnel,

In accordance with current Republic regulations, outposts are hereby informed of the authorized distribution of service medals to deserving NCR personnel. Detailed instructions regarding medal issuance and eligibility will be provided in a separate document.

Headquarters would also like to remind all personnel that the sale, trade, or unauthorized distribution of medals is strictly prohibited and may result in disciplinary sanctions. Medals are to remain within the custody of the outpost until formally awarded. Once issued, responsibility for the medal falls to the recipient.

These commendations are intended to recognize service, sacrifice, and dedication to the New California Republic. Personnel are expected to treat them with the respect they deserve.[/color]
